CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 18, 1956, pg. A1, reads: "Training and Defense - Warrant Officer Wilson, Capt. Robert L. Fritz, officer in charge of all units of the 724th anti-aircraft battalion and its fire control officer, and Lieut. Lucien Dale, commander of Battery 'D' discuss training and defense plans before visiting the installation in the Kenmawr area near the Greater Pittsburgh Airport. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Warrant Officer Wallace S. Wilson, Capt. Robert L. Fritz, and Lieut. Lucien Dale wearing military uniforms standing behind sign shaped liked arrow inscribed "PENNA DBTRY 724 AAA BN. NAT. GUARD" at Pennsylvania National Guard, Battery D, Kenmawr, Pennsylvania
